<#
.SYNOPSIS
  Powershell script which disables of the Secondary Logon service. This service allows users to run commands and programs with alternate credentials, typically giving them elevated privileges in a 
  standard user session. Disabling this service helps prevent privilege escalation and reduces the risk of credential theft in enterprise environments

.NOTES
    Author          : Andres Torres
    LinkedIn        : linkedin.com/in/andres-torres-richardson
    GitHub          : github.com/CyberTechTorres
    Date Created    : 2025-11-15
    Last Modified   : 2025-11-15
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN11-00-000175

.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 
    Tested By       : 
    Systems Tested  : 
    PowerShell Ver. : 

.USAGE
    Put any usage instructions here.
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\STIG:WN11-00-000175.ps1
#>
# Stop the 'Secondary Logon' service if it is running
Stop-Service -Name 'seclogon' -Force

# Set the startup type of 'Secondary Logon' service to Disabled
Set-Service -Name 'seclogon' -StartupType Disabled
